# PWA / desktop install (web prompt)

UnionOps offers desktop/app install via the **browser-native** Chromium “Install app” prompt (and Safari Add to Dock / Home Screen). There is **no** custom `beforeinstallprompt` UI.

## Surfaces

| Piece | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Manifest builder | `src/lib/pwa/manifest.ts` → `src/app/manifest.ts` |
| Host gate | `src/lib/pwa/hosts.ts` — only `unionops.org` / `www` |
| SW sync | `src/lib/pwa/register.ts` → `ServiceWorkerRegister` |
| Offline stub | `public/sw.js` — keep `CACHE`/`PRECACHE` in sync with `src/lib/pwa/shell.ts` |
| Quiet user guide | `/install` — footer muted link + support/privacy cross-links; **not** Header/Learn/Tools |

## When changing PWA or related features

1. Update `src/lib/pwa/*` first; keep `public/sw.js` string-identical for cache/precache.
2. Run `npm run test:unit` — must include `src/lib/pwa/*.test.ts` (hosts, register, manifest installability, shell↔sw sync, i18n).
3. If you touch `/install` or footer/support/privacy links, keep the page **out of** Header menus (see `comms-public-nav.mdc`).
4. Do **not** register the SW on localhost/CI; Playwright uses `serviceWorkers: "block"`.
5. Preserve installability: `name`/`short_name`, `start_url`, `display: standalone` (or fullscreen/minimal-ui), 192 + 512 icons.

## Do not

- Add an App Store / Microsoft Store wrapper without an explicit product decision
- Promote `/install` into main nav or Learn/Tools dropdowns
- Drop unit coverage when refactoring manifest, hosts, or `sw.js`
